- Mon 29 Apr 2019. DRC: 22 new confirmed cases and 17 deaths
[Actualite, in French, trans. Corr.SB, abridged, edited]
https://actualite.cd/2019/04/29/ebola-rdc-22-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-et-17-deces
[Byline: Christine Tshibuyi]

A total of 22 confirmed cases of Ebola virus disease were reported on Sun 28 Apr 2019 in the Butembo, Katwa, Mabalako, Mandima, Kalunguta, Beni, and Musienene areas in North Kivu and Ituri provinces, plagued by the Ebola outbreak since 1 Aug 2018, said the Ministry of Health also reporting "17 new confirmed case deaths".

The 17 deaths were recorded in Kalunguta (3), Katwa (5), Mandima (2), Butembo (5), Musienene (1), Mabalako (1), details the ministry in its bulletin.

The epidemic reported in North Kivu province before touching neighboring Ituri, has already caused 931 deaths including 865 among the 1373 confirmed cases, according to the latest count of the Ministry.

Moreover "410 people" have already been cured of Ebola but "263 suspected cases" are under investigation.

Health workers engaged in the response are also vulnerable. In total, 93 of them were infected by the virus and 33 died [update 2 May 2019].

Read also:
https://www.actualite.cd/2019/04/27/ebola-rdc-face-la-persistance-de-lepidemie-tshisekedi-cree-un-comite-multisectoriel-de [in French]

