[3] Worsening situation
- Tue 30 Apr 2019. Rise in case numbers
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5787

The rise in positive cases of Ebola patients in Butembo and surrounding areas continues to raise several concerns. According to Dr. Nestor Lubi, who was contacted from Brussels in Belgium, attacking experts, doctors, nurses, and health services who deal with this disease is endangering not only our population but also the republic.

The outbreak of confirmed cases is sometimes due to the resistance by some people to observe certain prevention rules. For Dr. Nestor Lubi, a Congolese doctor and teacher living in Brussels, Belgium, the public must take the threats of this disease seriously -- a disease that is endangering the population of the region. For this doctor, the population must combine its efforts in the fight against this disease.

"We must not be dispersed before this epidemic. The disease exists. And the Ebola virus kills. If we do not pay attention, she [it, i.e., the disease] will continue to kill. If there was a group of Mai-Mai behind the attacks of the Ebola treatment centers, they must understand that at this level they are irresponsible. If they were manipulated by a politician, they need to ask the politician what type of solution he is going to propose immediately to the people of our country to avoid illness. Because destroying health centers, attacking experts, doctors, nurses, health services who deal with this disease is endangering not only our population but also the republic. We may end up in quarantine. I would like to add the last thing. We already have a problem with ADF [rebel group], we do not need to add more," said Dr. Nestor Lubi from Brussels.

--
