- Mon 29 Apr 2019. Beni: 2nd outbreak of Ebola at Mabuku Hospital
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://protect2.fireeye.com/url?k=de160220-822ea542-de14fb15-000babd9f75c-00d753a3348783e7&u=http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5779

A 2nd case of Ebola virus disease has occurred in the Mabuku hospital center in the rural health zone of Kalunguta in the territory of Beni on Sat 27 Apr 2019. The patient had fled the health center Mambombo in the health zone Mabalako. He then went to a health post in Mabuku, where he spent a week before going to Mabuku Hospital where he died.

"For me it's really bad because the patient really came [at the last minute]. Just when we wanted to do first aid, it was already very serious. Just after, he arrived on 27 Apr 2019 at 1 am, he is dead. Then, as in the habit, we must always take on the dead. When we sent out for testing, a positive Ebola result was returned. Which worried us more; and it was found that the patient came from Ngazi. It was there that he was treated a week ago before arriving here in Mabuku. That's how we got a 2nd case here in Mabuku," said Dr. Kamoto of Mabuku Hospital Center.

Meanwhile, the vaccination went well at Mabuku Hospital. A total of 20 people were vaccinated. The low participation of contacts or of some who have been denied has been noted. And Dr. Kamoto is shocked. "Others who are also concerned are avoiding the vaccine and saying that it does not concern them, while the disease exists. People need to understand that the vaccine is there to prevent," he said.

FARDC soldiers and suspected Mai-Mai militia have secured this vaccination campaign.

